<ab>45. Artists, Scholars, Monarchs and Commanders, <lb/>
in brief, have ascended to fame and esteem <lb/>
by suppressing laziness,<lb/>
and hard effort and glorious acts. <lb/>
We should not get far in the world <lb/>
without the sound practice of work, <lb/>
the fruits of which provide utility, repose and joy.<lb/>

</ab>

<ab>
