<ab>46. Hearing this, O Youths, follow the road<lb/>
of work as swiftly as possible, for the end is sweet.<lb/>
Paint, draw, scribble, freely blot any sheet<lb/>
of Paper as if it waits for it.  <lb/>
Steal arms, legs, bodies, hands, feet –<lb/>
nothing is forbidden here. Those who want to<lb/>
must play the role of Rapiamus well.<lb/>
Well-cooked turnips make good soup.<lb/>


</ab>

