<ab>47. Try to escape the Poetic art of Rhetoric,<lb/>
with its charming ways, however desirable and sweet.<lb/>
I myself have not done a great deal to avoid it,<lb/> 
but it has often deterred me <lb/>
from the path of Painting, which is to be feared.<lb/>	
It is indeed a lovely flower; if it bore fruit<lb/>
and provided flour ready for the Kitchen,<lb/>
then the urge to use it would come. <lb/>


 </ab>

<ab>
<margin>right-middle</margin>
Rhetoric, a lovely flower without fruit, is discouraged because of the jealousy of painting.
</ab>

