<ab>49.  Begin suckling at the pure breasts <lb/>
of the ingenious maiden who bears weapons<lb/>
and came from Jupiter 's brain, as the Poets say,<lb/>
then bow willingly to general opinion.<lb/>
In this regard, keep company with <i>Apelles</i>,<lb/> 
for you will often acquire something <lb/>
–when you lend a patient ear– <lb/>
which was unknown to you before.<lb/>

 </ab>

<ab>
